Type: Package
Package: coLCA
Title: Convenience functions to complement package 'poLCA'
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Naoko", "Skiada", , "naoko.skiada@kcl.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8575-9846"))
Maintainer: The package maintainer <naoko.skiada@kcl.ac.uk>
Description: This package adds convenience functions to the
    'poLCA' package as well as some additional statistics.  
    New statistics: calculations of the consistent Akaike
    Information Criterion (cAIC), sample-adjusted Bayesian Information
    Criterion (aBIC), and the Lo-Mendel-Rubin Likelihood Ratio test
    (LMR LRT). Convenicence functions: a function that estimates all the
    latent class models with different number of classes required by the user.
    A function that takes this output and creates a comparison
    table of model selection statistics.
